editorialNotes.tagline: A fun way to learn a language
editorialNotes.standard: With its friendly approach and awesome updates, Duolingo’s long been one of our favourite apps for learning another language. Its secret: making the process genuinely fun. Engaging mini-games test your reading, writing and speaking skills, and joining a club (where you can encourage and compete with others) adds a great social element. Bonus: all those languages and games are available for free!
editorialNotes.short: Learn a new language. Join a club, chat with bots and get reminders to practice.

editorialNotes.standard: An app parents won’t have to mute in a restaurant, this is a free-play feast with switches to flip, gears to grind, and blobs to plop together. Endlessly inventive, it’s a master class in how a simple app can sometimes feel the most advanced.

You use all kinds of specialized equipment at the gym to keep your body in shape, but what about your brain? Peak is a comprehensive collection of exercises designed to hone your memory, sharpen your problem-solving skills, enhance your mental agility, and more. Daily workouts covering up to five areas of focus will leave your mind feeling limber, and you can track your results over time and even compare them to other Peak users in your age group. Best of all, mental gymnastics don’t cause painful brain-sprains.
editorialNotes.short: Exercise your mental agility—your focus, memory and coordination.
